programme.desc: Nancy has now recovered from a long illness and is ready to reenter the workforce. Our experts give her the polish and edge she will need to land a new position. Will Nancy go from"left on the shelf" to being a"hot commodity" and look ten years young.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Blackbelt Beauty
programme.desc: Donna is a former Marine, a karate brown belt and a single mom with not much time for herself. Donna enters her journey with her "No Pain, No Gain" Marine attitude, and surrenders to The Glam Squad and their team of experts.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Trials of Tracy
programme.desc: Tracy is a New York City lawyer who can't find a man. Her frumpy wardrobe and thick glasses keep her home buried in her books for fear of rejection. But our team is on the case to bring this lonely lawyer out of her shell and gain some needed confidence.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Jayne Lowe
programme.desc: Woking wife and mother Jayne Lowe is at an all time low. After a high-flying career as an air-hostess, she has come down to earth with a bump, as a stay-at-home mum of three under-five's. Can Nicki Hambleton-Jones make Jayne look ten years younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Reconstructing Bernie
programme.desc: A construction worker by trade, Bernie is a man's man. So while years of backbreaking labor in the sun has taken its toll on his body, Bernie hasn't been taking care of himself. Time to make Bernie look 10 Years Younger!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Donna Fuller
programme.desc: Derby wife and mum Donna Fuller is stuck at home and stuck in a rut. Her biggest problem is her gapped front teeth, which have left her, literally, with nothing to smile about. Can Nicky Hambleton-Jones and the team make Debbie look 10 years younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Bikini Special - Heather Williams
programme.desc: NHS Manager Heather Williams is the perfect candidate: after a weight loss of five stones and three years of four times a week gym workouts, all that remained of her former size 20 body was a sack of excess skin covering a tiny 4 foot eleven frame.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Singing A New Tune
programme.desc: April lost a front tooth in a horseback riding accident and never smiles. Her passion is singing, and she'd like to stand on stage without embarrassment. Will an orthodontic overhaul and a full Glam assault drop years from her appearance?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Independence Day
programme.desc: Recently divorced and about to send her daughter off to college, Candice is embarking on a new phase in life. Alone and worried about feeling old and unattractive, Candice has come for help to boost her spirits.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Debbie Ashcroft "One Year On"
programme.desc: 46 year old Debbie Ashcroft was a lifelong smoker and sunbed addict with the peculiar habit of bleaching her hair up to six times a week. A year later Nicky visits Debbie to find out if she's permanently kicked all the bad habits.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Sewing The Seeds To A New Look
programme.desc: Melissa has the perfect Beverly Hills fashion career, working with the finest made-to-order clothing. But when the exclusive clientele see her missing teeth, the impression is not what she would like. She also desperately wants to update her look.
programme.sub-title: Sewing The Seeds To A New Look

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: 80 lbs. Down, 10 Years To Go
programme.desc: After struggling with health issues Cheryl has recently lost 80 pounds and needs her appearance to catch up to her body. She is single and ready to start dating again. Cheryl's new makeover will help her hit the dating scene with a renewed attitude.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Grey Skies To Blue
programme.desc: Between her busy family life, and a scrapbook business on the side, Christine barely has time for herself. After 20 years of marriage and three kids, she's in need of a makeover and some serious rekindled romance.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: A Prescription For Youth
programme.desc: New Mom Amber has her work cut out for her. In her early teens she was diagnosed with Crohn's disease, which resulted in unwanted physical side effects. Watch the team of experts make Amber look 10 Years Younger.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1
programme.desc: The Trevanions have been living at Leopard's Den for over a year. The wildlife is roaming freely and the family are settled into African way of life. Business however is not good. With an abundance of game lodges competition is fierce.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2
programme.desc: It's the grand reopening of Mara and a British wildlife charity is using the event to release a vulture back into the wild. Fatani, the new, young and ambitious manager of Mara has hired Danny as the vet to oversee the release.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Leopard's Den is looking after a sick and orphaned baby elephant called Togo. However, despite Evan and Du Plessis' constant vigil, Togo is dying from a broken heart. Evan is distraught and Du Plessis promises they will look after her together.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: Sarah's absence couldn't have come at a worse time for Leopard's Den. Nature Conservation is carrying out their annual inspection and everything has to be tip top. Danny's determined they pass with flying colours and everyone is roped in to help.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: Everyone's excited at the prospect of Leopard's Den's new arrival. Bash, Danny's old tutor and Rosie's Godfather, is coming from England to help Danny grow his veterinary practice.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6
programme.desc: The Trevanions are delighted when Fatani asks Danny to take an aggressive hippo off his hands. As they prepare for its arrival Sarah gets a bit of a shock when her mother Caroline beats the hippo to the post.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 7
programme.desc: Business is looking up at Leopard's Den but Sarah is feeling agitated. Caroline thinks it because Simon, her ex husband and Evan and Olivia's Dad, is arriving from England to get married. But Sarah has other things on her mind.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 8
programme.desc: Danny is undertaking a drugs trial at Leopard's Den. But de-worming wildebeest isn't Caroline's idea of fun. She hates animals and finds the whole business mind-numbingly boring.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 7
programme.desc: The chopper team are about to take off to rescue a seriously injured man.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: 55-year-old Gold Coast holidaymaker Irina is in real trouble - she's caught in a deadly ocean rip. Like many tourists, Irena was unaware of the risks of not swimming between the beach flags. The Gold Coast rescue helicopter spots her in the nick of time.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: A head-on car collision in Tasmania has left tourists Hong and Xeu Wu fighting for their lives. Ambulance crews have managed to stabilize Mr. Wu but Mrs. Wu is in a critical condition and calling out for her husband.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: A team of amateur scuba divers find themselves in deep trouble when their boat capsizes off Sydney's Botany Bay. The Westpac La Perouse crew spots the distressed divers while on a routine training mission.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: 65-year old Dave, a surf skier, is attacked and bitten by a Great White shark while training in the ocean. Dehydrated (after four days at sea), Margo needs urgent hospital care.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: A car crashes another car at a country intersection. It's situation critical with four people trapped. It turns out someone was running from the police – and he was on drugs.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 8
programme.desc: The chopper team is responding to a life threatening emergency.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 9
programme.desc: The team have received a status 2 callout; Mark Lorimer was knocked out and has multiple injuries after being hit head-on by another vehicle.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 10
programme.desc: The team are called to a road accident where a woman has been cut from inside of her wrecked car.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 11
programme.desc: The team is responding to a life-threatening emergency. A cyclist in his 60s, Terrence Williams, is unresponsive and critical after an accident 15 minutes flying time from Auckland, near the small settlement of Maramarua.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 12
programme.desc: The team are called out to a status 2 emergency; Clark Chamberlain was abseiling when he fell from the top of a cliff to the ground. He's now in a critical condition suffering from multiple injuries.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3
programme.desc: Tasmania Police is on high alert after a prisoner escapes from jail. The man is armed and dangerous. The Rescue Helicopter is called in to assist with the manhunt. Things turn deadly when they spot him.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: Hiker Robert had trained for over 6 months for the remote Cradle Mountain bush walk. With his young daughter in tow they set off on a 48 km walk. Three hours into the walk Roberts health takes a turn for the worse.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: A young man has flipped his quad bike and can't move his neck. Later that night, the crew is called to a suburban house because a DIY homebuilder has fallen through the roof in his house – and there's a bone sticking out through his jeans.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 6
programme.desc: The embassy visits a convicted drug dealer in the world's most notorious prison. But Steven claims he's the innocent victim of an undercover drug sting gone wrong.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 12
programme.desc: Great cars and pretty girls. The Nürburgring is shaking as the VLN begins its second leg of the tournament. We will be commentating on this exciting competition, as well as showing highlights of the BMW's 1st leg win.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 13
programme.desc: The fourth race of the VLN season is regarded as a dress rehearsal for the 24 hour race. For the top teams and best drivers this is the last opportunity for a real hard test.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 14
programme.desc: Today, we are going to look back at the highlight of last week. The 24 hour race - as always it was exciting. In addition 'Strong Man Run' and a look at the tourist drivers.

programme.title: Track Masters
programme.desc: Some heavy guns are going to be driven around the ring on today's show. We are at the Truck Grand Prix and shall be following the progress of driver Uwe Nittle as he gets ready for qualifying.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 16
programme.desc: On today's show, we will be taking a look at the RCN Challenge - the BMW Driving Experience. Also on the show, we will be paying a visit to the Devils Diner - the indoor meeting place for drivers on the ring!

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 17
programme.desc: Now that the 24-hour race is over we have left the Nürburgring and moved to Büren, Germany, where Räder Sport is based. Famous for really fast front-wheel drives, it provides a lot of horsepower down on the track.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 18

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 19
programme.desc: On today's episode, we are going old-timer crazy, like the Mercedes S for example with 160 horsepower that lead Rudolf Caracciola to victory in the 1927 opening race. Do not to miss this old-timer grand prix event!

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 20

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 21

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 22

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Dream Stalker
programme.desc: Street asks Liam to help a friend who's arrested for the murder of a man he hated. Liam talks to him and he claims that he dreamed of killing him.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Lost Generation

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: The Summit

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Street Chase

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Trapped by Time

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Atonement
programme.desc: Sandoval goes to Renee to request a trial to testify to atrocities against humanity committed by the Taelons. A manhunt for Sandoval begins when he quits and leaves the mother ship. Liam has to protect him on his way to the grand jury.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Blood Ties
programme.desc: Strange assaults and several deaths may be related to a Doors/Taelon joint venture where Taelon core energy was used to heal people. It appears that the energy is being sucked back out of the patients.

programme.desc: Mary Jane's hormones rage out of control after she gets an hCG shot. She's also offered an exclusive story from Sheldon DeWitt and further strains her already-strained friendship with Lisa. (S2, ep6)

programme.title: Tyler Perry's The Oval: The Dark Sheep
programme.desc: Hunter's reckless behavior becomes uncontrollable.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Paranormal Detour
programme.desc: With time off between cases, Ryan suggests to the PRS team they choose a random town to investigate. They roll into St. Helens, Oregon, home of Twilight, where they learn about the long history of the paranormal in the area.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Messenger
programme.desc: Kelli and her husband Riley are frightened in their coastal Oregon home. They are plagued by a headless apparition and often hear mysterious noises that resemble cries for help from the dark corners of their house.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Asylum
programme.desc: PRS explores a New York State Prison that was once a mental asylum. Ryan and his team go behind bars to uncover the institution's paranormal past and present.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Boy Pushed Me
programme.desc: Bruce and Danielle are terrified by an EVP recorded in their Indiana home stating "Kill them." Even more chilling, their toddler son survived a fall out of a window only to tell his parents, "Boy pushed me."

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Haunted Piano
programme.desc: Ryan and the PRS team are called in when unlucky antique collectors unwittingly bring a paranormally-infested piano into their home. The team attempts to dismantle and destroy the offending instrument.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Supernatural Seduction
programme.desc: PRS investigates the Campbell House, where the Innkeeper and guests claim to have sexual encounters with a spirit who has deep ties to a family tragedy.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Drowned
programme.desc: Kim and her family have been frightened out of their seaside Maryland home. Multiple family members have reported sightings of children with purple lips and strange noises emanating from the nearby creek.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Spirits of the Slave Dungeon
programme.desc: Ryan books a two-night case in a real haunted jail in Charleston, SC, but PRS soon realizes the spirits themselves are being held there against their will and subjected to an unjust form of torture.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Requiem
programme.desc: A young woman named Kristy has been haunted in her own bedroom since she can remember. Now it's up to Ryan and the crew to help Kristy before she's overwhelmed by the entity.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Knickerbocker
programme.desc: PRS checks into the Knickerbocker Hotel in Linesville, Pennsylvania where the owners are reporting strange noises and the appearance of phantom children in some of the rooms.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Beer, Wine and Spirits
programme.desc: Brian's bar has a cranky customer who's got a bad habit of breaking wine glasses. Charlie has been dead since prohibition.

programme.title: Paranormal State: If I Should Die...
programme.desc: Proven paranormal investigator Ken Arrington leads a new class of characters as they try to help a family cope with what appears to be a demonic spirit in their home.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Invitation to Evil
programme.desc: Paula and her husband Mike are under siege by a purported shadow demon in their North Carolina home. Paula has witnessed a toddler bed levitating and heard deep growls. Michelle, Ryan and the team uncover the shocking truth behind the haunting.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Dark Man
programme.desc: A grieving mother suspects her deceased son may have fallen victim to a mysterious entity called The Dark Man.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Vegas
programme.desc: The PRS travels to Sin City to investigate a 14-year old medium who claims to speak to a dead girl.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Dartford Library
programme.desc: Dartford Library comes under Yvette and the crew's scrutiny as they experience strange poltergeist activity involving books, and contact the denizens that appear to cling to the building.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Stockport Workhouse
programme.desc: The Stockport Workhouse opened on a bleak Christmas Day in 1841 and quickly filled with the desperate and jobless. The Dickensian atmosphere gives Yvette and the team a night to remember!

programme.title: Most Haunted: Tatton Park, Old Hall
programme.desc: Journalist Carol Thatcher joins the team as they journey to Tatton Old Hall. They investigate reports of a misogynistic presence as well as a mischievous spirit who plays tricks on the unwary.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Cammell Laird
programme.desc: Untimely death, fear and vast emptiness await the team in Merseyside. They investigate the offices and huge construction hall of what was once the heart of the Cammell Laird shipyard.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Sutton House
programme.desc: Musician and amateur ghost hunter Lee Ryan joins Yvette as the team encounter poltergeists, fear and phantoms at Sutton House. They find a veritable treasure trove of reported paranormal activity.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Tatton Park Mansion
programme.desc: The crew investigates Tatton Park Mansion. There is so much reported paranormal activity within its walls that certain phantoms must walk the grounds because there is no room for them inside.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Matlock Bath Pavilion
programme.desc: The team travels to the spa town of Matlock Bath to investigate strange phenomena in the pavilion. Once a tourist destination, it is now home to a mining museum, a night club and ghostly apparitions.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Country Doctor
programme.desc: A country doctor refuses to slow down and seems to be working himself to death.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Time in a Bottle
programme.desc: A district attorney clashes with a lawyer who agrees to defend a friend charged with stealing.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Back to Oakland
programme.desc: Mark returns to Oakland to become a police officer again, and is reunited with his old partner. However, he discovers his old beat has become a storm of racial hatred.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: We Have Forever - Part 1
programme.desc: Jonathan hopes that he'll be released from his duties to be reunited with his former wife when she passes away.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: We Have Forever - Part 2
programme.desc: Jonathan hopes that he'll be released from his duties to be reunited with his former wife when she passes away.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Correspondent
programme.desc: A war correspondent finds himself imprisoned and facing execution. Meanwhile, Jonathan and Mark show him what's he's missed during his life by putting work ahead of family.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Aloha
programme.desc: A Hawaiian singer learns to overcome self-pity after being disabled in a truck accident.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: A Prescription For Youth
programme.desc: New Mom Amber has her work cut out for her. In her early teens she was diagnosed with Crohn's disease, which resulted in unwanted physical side effects. Watch the team of experts make Amber look 10 Years Younger.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Time to Face the Music
programme.desc: Akil is an unemployed music industry executive who feels like his under eye bags, to long dread locks and older looks are getting in the way of getting a new job. 10 Years Younger is on one of it's hardest missions to date!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Looking for Love Through All the Wrong Glasses
programme.desc: Will owns a successful real estate investment business, but he hasn't been as lucky in love. Will's phobia of doctors have kept him from losing his thick glasses and fixing his gnarled teeth. The bottom line is that Will hasn't had a date in years!
programme.sub-title: Looking for Love Through All the Wrong Glasses

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Belle Of The Ball
programme.desc: Raising a family on a military base, with a husband fighting in Iraq, has been an incredibly stressful situation for Melissa, a young stay at home mother. She realizes her appearance has taken a back seat for too long, and is willing to make a change.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Belle of the Bat Mitzvah
programme.desc: Traci is a busy housewife and stay-at-home mom, who along with caring for her three kids, a baby, and her husband, has the added stress of planning her daughter's upcoming Bat Mitzvah where she'll see guests she hasn't seen in 13 years!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Paul Turner
programme.desc: Paul Turner is a 37 year old pub landlord who looks like he's been to every party ever thrown and been the last one to leave every time. Help is on hand from presenter and stylist Nicky Hambleton-Jones and her expert team.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Sue Tomkins
programme.desc: Night shift worker Sue Tomkins has lost her sparkle. Lank hair, haggard wrinkles, sunken eyes and weary clothes are just the starting point for Nicky Hambleton-Jones and her team of experts who've got 10 days to knock 10 years off Sue's lifeless look.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: D-Nice
programme.desc: Dwayne hides his receding hairline and baggy eyes behind a baseball cap and shades. He is starting over, eager to find love and willing to let the Glam Squad point him in the right direction.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: It’s Like Pulling Teeth
programme.desc: Daniel Trnka is a man in constant pain. A rare hereditary defect has left his teeth crumbling and destroyed. Now, with a new younger bride, and baby daughter, Daniel wants to look his age before people mistake him for his daughter's grandfather.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Jeni Ingram
programme.desc: Well spoken Jeni Ingram lives life in the fast lane. Her complexion was left screaming for air and her teeth had all but crumbled away. Nicky Hambleton Jones and her team of experts take charge.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Aging 9-1-1
programme.desc: Joni, a hardworking 911 dispatcher on the night shift, struggles to keep up with her much younger-and much younger looking-husband. After she puts herself in expert hands for 10 days, will the new Joni wow her husband?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Heather Frederick
programme.desc: Heather Frederick isn't really as old as she appears. She's old before her time and it's up to Fiona and her team of experts to transform Heather from loveable granny to hot child in the city, in just 10 days.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Funny Girl
programme.desc: Growing up in a family of men, Beverly became one of the boys. Over the years she has struggled to find her own style, which has left her frustrated and ready for a change.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: New Mom, New Look
programme.desc: Cindy has an unusual family. Recently married to an older man, her stepchildren aren't much younger than she is. Her looks are failing her and Cindy now feels she no longer turns heads. Time to make Cindy look 10 Years Younger!

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 8
programme.desc: Danny is undertaking a drugs trial at Leopard's Den. But de-worming wildebeest isn't Caroline's idea of fun. She hates animals and finds the whole business mind-numbingly boring.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 9
programme.desc: Du Plessis is in a foul mood. It's his 60th birthday and he has no intentions of celebrating it. But the Trevanions have other ideas and Caroline is organising a surprise party.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 10
programme.desc: All is quiet at Leopard's Den as Sarah, Evan and Olivia gather at the hospital. Danny has been given the all clear to go home. But Du Plessis is still unconscious and seriously ill. Caroline keeps a tender vigil at his bedside.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1
programme.desc: New lodges nearly break the family, but they learn that it's the animals which make Leopard's Den a success.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2
programme.desc: Danny needs an assistant but fails to see that she's right under his nose; Sarah finds out that she needs her mum.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Leopard's Den expands and DuPlessis becomes a grandfather after a close-call with an angry elephant.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: Danny and Sarah let their past catch up with them, and Caroline and DuPlessis go shopping for lion-prey.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 6
programme.desc: The embassy visits a convicted drug dealer in the world's most notorious prison. But Steven claims he's the innocent victim of an undercover drug sting gone wrong.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 7
programme.desc: Young Rhys calls the embassy after his businessman father is arrested and jailed for fraud. Can Rhys raise the bail money to get him out of jail? It's a race against the clock.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 8
programme.desc: Ash contacts the embassy convinced he's going to die after days of partying. The notorious Thai bucket strikes again! The embassy needs to uncover the truth. Is he really in danger or is he suffering from alcohol poisoning?

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 1
programme.desc: Nathan is in Phuket on a holiday of a lifetime, fuelled by sun, sex and steroids, when disaster strikes. 19-year-old Paris is on a gap year adventure of a lifetime. But just two months into her first-ever overseas holiday she's hit a big roadblock.

programme.title: Perfect Vagina
programme.desc: Through our author's personal journey this documentary will explore this fascinating secret world and question what or who is fuelling women's desire to have perfect vaginas.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: De Anna and her husband were celebrating their 50th wedding anniversary on board a luxury liner. The ship's doctor radios for help. But the liner is a long way out at sea. Can the rescue crew get to De Anna in time?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: 14 year-old motor-cross rider, Kacee gets the death wobbles and cartwheels over the top of his handle bars and hits the ground head first. He's now struggling to breath and is barely able to talk. Team Air Rescue needs to get Kacee to the hospital fast.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: Fishing buddies Scott, Wayne and Wayne's son Andrew head out to their favorite fishing spot, but when a freak wave hits their boat they have no choice but to SOS for help. Within minutes, the boat capsizes. Can the Air Rescue crew get to them in time?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3
programme.desc: 71 year-old retired nurse Sandra was exploring Tasmania's Cradle Mountain when she slipped and fractured her wrist. She's in excruciating pain and night is falling. Visibility is dangerously low. Can the rescue team get in close enough to get them out?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: Mountain bike fanatic, Blake was out riding when he clipped a tree and crashed into a rock. It's a time critical rescue mission. And what the rescue crew doesn't yet know is that Blake is about to take a turn for the worse.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 13
programme.desc: The team are responding to reports of a life-or death emergency; Jim Te Whata has been pulled from the water cold, unconscious and not breathing.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 1
programme.desc: The Rescue 1 chopper team struggles to save two young men who are feared drowned at Hahei; a Coromandel motorcyclist is struggling with punctured lungs, and young man is trapped inside a car after a high speed accident.

programme.title: Tuning: Dodge / Mini Cooper / Porsche
programme.desc: The Dodge RAM is anything but cute. It is a true beast. The ram is the symbol of the Dodge brand and the eponym for a very special vehicle. The RAM pickup combines robustness and impulsiveness.

programme.title: Tuning: Lamborghini / Porsche / Jaguar
programme.desc: A supercharger from O.CT gives the Lamborghini Huracan, which is by no means underpowered, an additional 200 hp. This makes the super sports car the ultimate street-legal projectile.

programme.title: 4x4: Wildly through the desert
programme.desc: In 2010, BMW and the German racing team X-Raid decided to transform a Mini Countryman into an offroad-vehicle and participate in the world-famous Dakar Rally. Also: the Mercedes G63 AMG 6x6, a most exclusive, over-the-top 6-wheel off-road monster...

programme.title: 4x4: Trendy City - SUVs
programme.desc: City-SUVs are the latest trend in the automotive world. They aren't necessarily made for offroad terrain but attract customers through their modern and urban design. In this episode, the Subaru XV shows its offroad skills, and the Nissan Juke is take…

programme.title: 4x4: Land Rover Special
programme.desc: The Land Rover Defender is one of the oldest offroad car models. It may be loud and uncomfortable, but it's absolutely authentic in its simplicity. We took a look at this iconic vehicle and 70 years of Land Rover history.

programme.title: 4x4: Extraordinary SUVs
programme.desc: This Mitsubishi Outlander Plug-In Hybrid is the world's first hybrid SUV with two electric motors and a 2-liter combustion engine. We tested if such a combination makes sense for offroad vehicles. Also: the Chevrolet Silverado...

programme.title: 4x4: SUV Girlpower
programme.desc: Nancy and Nadia, two daring Jordanian women faced the challenge to cross the Moroccan desert in a Hummer H3. The two professional racers took part in the Conti 4x4 Trophy - a demanding rally through the Atlas Mountains and the Western Sahara.

programme.title: 4x4: SUV Concepts
programme.desc: Before Bentley and Jaguar started producing their own luxury SUV models, the two British brands presented their take on this special range of cars. We took a look at their concept cars, the Bentley EXP 9F and Jaguar's C-X17.

programme.title: 4x4: Normal vs. Lifestyle SUVs
programme.desc: The SUVs Nissan X-Trail and BMW X4 certainly aren't typical offroaders. We witnessed Nissan's presentation of their new X-Trail model and the BMW X4 world premiere in Bilbao. Also: the Steinbeißer Trophy...

programme.title: 4x4: American SUVs
programme.desc: In the United States, SUVs aren't usually considered simple workhorses but rather treated as regular everyday vehicles. US-Americans don't want to miss out on space, comfort and loading capacity. Their motto is: the bigger, the better.

programme.title: 4x4: Tuned SUVs
programme.desc: SUVs usually are rather impressive right out of the factory, but there are many tuning and customizing options: huge wheels, crazy colors and perfomance similar to super sports cars. One might ask if such alterations are really necessary, but enthusi…

programme.title: 4x4: Small, strong, stylish
programme.desc: At first glance, compact cars like the Audi A1, the Volkswagen Golf and the Mini don't seem to belong in this series, but when the "A1" becomes the "S1" and the Golf gets a "R" in its name, these small cars turn into all-wheel beasts.

programme.title: 4x4: Fascination offroad
programme.desc: At the All-Wheel Adventure in Bad Kissingen, Germany, the biggest exhibition for offroaders in Europe, we test drove the Rallye Defender and examined how a regular Jeep Wrangler with only a few modifications could double in price.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Manifesto
programme.desc: A cabin on the slopes of Pikes Peak catches fire, and a young sheriff’s deputy is posted to guard the scene overnight--then he’s found dead in his patrol car the next morning.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Joker In the Pack
programme.desc: A card game is interrupted by gunfire, leaving a young man dead. Lt. Joe Kenda soon learns the seeds of his destruction were sewn earlier the same day.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Bad Moon Rising
programme.desc: Night before Halloween, a real-life nightmare unfolds when a young man is found clinging to life. The case takes a dark turn when Lt. Joe Kenda learns there is a second victim somewhere in the woods.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Death Comes Knocking
programme.desc: Neighbors are aghast when Ernestine Addison and her teen son Bobby are gunned down in cold blood. The case heats up when Kenda receives word that the killer’s murderous rampage isn’t over just yet.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Written in Blood
programme.desc: A community is shocked when Antoine McKenzie is brazenly shot outside an auto parts store in broad daylight. The only lead left for Lt. Joe Kenda is a final message written in the victim’s own blood.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: After School Special
programme.desc: Tragedy strikes when a beloved teacher is poisoned in her classroom. As doctors fight to save Barbara Lewis’ life, Lt. Joe Kenda and his team delve into her personal affairs.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Eyes Wide Shut
programme.desc: A park ranger discovers the corpse of amateur boxer Corey Edge floating in a shallow creek. Kenda learns the victim had ties to the criminal underworld, and investigates a rogue’s gallery of hustlers.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: My First Case
programme.desc: In his first case with the homicide unit, rookie burglary detective Joe Kenda volunteers to work a bloody multi-victim shooting deemed “unsolvable” by the veterans.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Hyde & Vada and Nacho
programme.desc: Hyde and Vada, both wolf hybrids have aggression issues to work out especially when it comes to other dogs. Nacho, bit a child, and shows aggression when he has his toy.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Bikini, Fella, Winston and Oliver
programme.desc: Bull terrier won't behave at home and has irrational fear of grooming; Jack Russell / Italian Greyhound mix cries and barks whenever left alone; a police officer's Yorkies are disturbing the peace.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Maxwell, Brooklyn, and Tipper
programme.desc: A spoiled Welsh Sealyham Terrier has dominance issues; an excitable English Mastiff has behavioral issues, and a territorial Tibetan Terrier needs help accepting other dogs.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Riley & Sophie, Aussie and Lulu, Bebe, & Sasha
programme.desc: A couple of adopted basset hounds have a bad case of sibling rivalry. A dingo mix from Australia hasn't adjusted to her new life in California. An overly protective poodle.
programme.sub-title: Riley & Sophie, Aussie and Lulu, Bebe, & Sasha

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Reggie, Diva, Rocco, & Vito, and Mugsy
programme.desc: Meet a feral dog who likes to guard pregnant horses on a ranch. English bulldog Rocco joins an existing pack and targets one of his brothers. A rescued pit bull terrier is a couch potato.
programme.sub-title: Reggie, Diva, Rocco, & Vito, and Mugsy

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Cotton, Ricky, and Lila & Duke
programme.desc: An American Eskimo watchdog who takes his role too far; a Shibu Inu with a mean streak; a boxer who was attached by another dog one day in the park, and has since become more aggressive.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Tenacious B
programme.desc: A French Bulldog is anxious around other dogs, and a Vizsla is afraid of cars. Can Cesar help one dog improve his social skills and steer the other's behavior toward the fast lane?

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Special: 100th Episode Celebration
programme.desc: Participants from more than 200 stories featured on Dog Whisperer parade down the red carpet to celebrate the 100th Episode of Dog Whisperer with Cesar Millan.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Eats Detergent/Strongman
programme.desc: 19-year-old Tempestt eats detergent up to seven times a day, not to mention the soap she eats in the shower. Meanwhile, Jeff is addicted to strongman competitions training up to six hours a day.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Sucker/Bodybuilder
programme.desc: Lauren was once addicted to drugs and alcohol, but now is addicted to body-building, which may have caused long term health problems. Meanwhile, Rhonda has been addicted to sucking her thumb ever since her parents divorced when she was a child.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Hair Puller/Shoe Fanatic
programme.desc: Showcases a woman addicted to shoes, while another is addicted to pulling her hair and eating the follicle.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Eats Couch Cushion/Furry
programme.desc: While battling her addiction to eating couch cushions, Adele has destroyed 7 couches and 2 chairs. Meanwhile, Lauren is more comfortable in her fur suit than in her own skin.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Ventriloquist/Cat Lady
programme.desc: April's addiction to her puppets has gotten so strong she can't go anywhere without them. Debbie is severely allergic to cats, but has over twenty of them, leaving her in isolation.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Can’t Stop Cleaning/Love Rocks
programme.desc: Cyntrelle dropped out of high school because of her addiction to cleaning. Belinda's obsession with rocks has taken over her life, with more than 100,000 scattered around her home.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Eats Rocks/Pillow Obsessed
programme.desc: Theresa has been eating rocks for more than 20 years and can't stop. Meanwhile, Tamara carries around her childhood pillow Boo everywhere she goes.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Bathes in Bleach/Eats Plastic
programme.desc: Kailyn has eaten plastic every day for more than eleven years, consuming more than 150 pounds. Meanwhile, Gloria, 28, has taken her addiction to bleach to the extreme by bathing in it daily.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Carrying My Husband’s Urn
programme.desc: Casie has been so shocked by the sudden death of her husband, Shawn, that she takes his urn everywhere she goes. But she has now started eating his ashes.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Eats Cat Food/Smells Moth Balls
programme.desc: Mary has taken her addiction to cat food to the extreme, consuming 900 cat treats and several cans of food every day. Meanwhile, Alicia has been addicted to smelling mothballs for 15 years.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Sniffs Pine Cleaner/Road Kill Addict
programme.desc: Jillian is addicted to smelling pine cleaner and can't go more than 15 minutes without a fix, using up to six bottles a week. Scott is obsessed with picking up dead animals from the road.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Drinks Urine
programme.desc: Carrie has been addicted to drinking her urine for four years. She drinks about 80 ounces a day with belief it has helped treat her cancer. Can Carrie's daughters persuade her to see a physician?

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Drinks Gasoline / Carries Doll Head
programme.desc: Shannon is addicted to gasoline, drinking about 15 teaspoons every day. Lacey has been carrying and smelling her doll head "Suzie Q" everywhere she goes.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: In Love With Balloons/Face Mask Eater
programme.desc: Julius has been sexually attracted to balloons for decades and keeps more than fifty thousand in his home at all times. Natasha eats entire jars of clay face masks every day.
programme.sub-title: In Love With Balloons/Face Mask Eater

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Million Dollar Manor
programme.desc: Born and raised in the bayou, Floyd and Robin Foti are living the American Dream. Their small business grew to become a massive food market. Now they’re looking for a million dollar home.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: All-Terrain Livin
programme.desc: Josh and Tiffany Chambless grew up living the bayou lifestyle and spending any spare moment exploring the swamps on their ATVs. Now, they’re looking for a place that’s baby friendly.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Wake Zone Getaway
programme.desc: Ross and Sarah want a new bayou home where they can walk out their front door onto their fishing boat. They discover a house on an island can make getting there tough.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Cajun Cabins
programme.desc: Pat and Joyce want their own slice of the southern frontier. They're looking for a hunting cabin that has the wilderness he wants, but the space she desires.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Redneck Riviera
programme.desc: Spear fisherman Clay and his girlfriend Jackie are looking for their first home together around Pensacola, Florida, an area where the bayou meets the beach, known as the Redneck Riviera.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Mississippi High Rises
programme.desc: Matthew and Lindsey are looking for a camp of their own. Lake Mary houses can flood, so the couple is looking for a high rise home, lifted 20 feet off the ground!

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Backwoods Paradise
programme.desc: Life in the bayou is all about family and passing down traditions. Blane is looking for a place where he can spend quality time with his teenage daughter, doing what their family does best – hunting.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Beached, Bayous, Backwoods
programme.desc: Jamie and his fiancée Brandi are looking for a home to start their life together near Gulf Shores, Alabama. But there’s one problem – Jamie wants a house on the bayou, but Brandi prefers the beach.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Mud Loving Camps
programme.desc: Trey and Jacob are two best friends who want to buy a backwoods getaway home for them and their families. They discover properties where the fields have been flooded to attract wild birds.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Burbs to the Bayou
programme.desc: Marty and Shelly grew up in the backwoods of the Mississippi bayou. But recently they’ve been stuck in the suburbs. So now they’re looking for a new home that will get them back into wilderness.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Biloxi Jackpot
programme.desc: Childhood sweethearts, Rowdy and Stevi, want to move into a starter home on the bayou. They love the excitement of nightlife and gambling so they’re looking for a house close to Biloxi’s casinos.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Cajun Inventor
programme.desc: High school sweethearts Donnie and Laurie have dreamed of having a weekend fishing camp on the bayou for as long as they can remember. Now, that dream can become a reality.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: City Girl and Bayou Boy
programme.desc: Newly engaged couple - Barrett and Haley - are looking for their first home on the bayou, but there’s one problem: he’s from the country and she’s from the city, so they’re sure to butt heads.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Off The Beaten Bayou
programme.desc: David and Blair love getting out on the waters of the Louisiana Bayou, so they want a weekend waterfront getaway home. But these houses come with their own hassles.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Striking It Rich
programme.desc: Carter and his wife Colleen have made millions from the bayou oil industry, so now they want a million dollar home on the water. In the bayou, that kind of money can buy luxury.
